SL
()LN
EL
SL
(NAME)LN
EL
SL
(     CalcBond - calculate bonds between close atoms)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(SYNOPSIS)LN
EL
SL
(     CalcBond expr \( 0 | 1 \) \( 0 | 1 \))LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(DESCRIPTION)LN
EL
SL
(     Find pairs of selected atoms that have a small)LN
EL
SL
(     distance, but are not connected by a bond. An atom )LN
EL
SL
(     pair is a candiate if the distance is less than the)LN
EL
SL
(     sum of the bond radii stored in the file:)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(         $MOLMOLHOME/setup/AtomRadius)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     Depending on the options, the command will create)LN
EL
SL
(     a report with the missing bonds, will add them to)LN
EL
SL
(     the structure, or both. Only bonds that appear in)LN
EL
SL
(     a minimal number of structures given as first)LN
EL
SL
(     argument appear in the report.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     In the report produced by this command, a table of)LN
EL
SL
(     bonds will be created for each set of molecules with)LN
EL
SL
(     the same structure. A '+' sign indicates that the)LN
EL
SL
(     bond was detected in the molecule corresponding to)LN
EL
SL
(     the column. The '+' sign is replaced by a '5' for)LN
EL
SL
(     molecules 5, 15, 25, ... and by a '0' for molecules)LN
EL
SL
(     10, 20, 30, ...)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     This command is useful after reading a PDB file that)LN
EL
SL
(     contains unknown residues, or a DG file with)LN
EL
SL
(     unknown residues and missing connection informations.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     This command supports groups.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(EXAMPLE)LN
EL
SL
(     CalcBond 5 1 0)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(SEE ALSO)LN
EL
SL
(     PathNames, ReadPdb, ReadDg, Group, AddBond)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(DATE)LN
EL
SL
(     981101)LN
EL

