SL
()LN
EL
SL
(NAME)LN
EL
SL
(     CalcDist - find short distances between atoms)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(SYNOPSIS)LN
EL
SL
(     CalcDist expr expr expr)LN
EL
SL
(         \( 0 | 1 \) \( 0 | 1 \) \( 0 | 1 \) \( 0 | 1 \))LN
EL
SL
(         [ name ] [ name ])LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(DESCRIPTION)LN
EL
SL
(     Find pairs of selected atoms that have a distance)LN
EL
SL
(     smaller than the one given as first argument, but are)LN
EL
SL
(     not connected over one or two bonds.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     Distances between residues that are closer in)LN
EL
SL
(     sequence than given by the second arument are not)LN
EL
SL
(     considered.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The first option determines whether distances)LN
EL
SL
(     within structures or distances between atoms of)LN
EL
SL
(     different structures are desired.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The second option determines whether a report with)LN
EL
SL
(     short distances is created.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The third option determines whether a peak list)LN
EL
SL
(     \(XEASY format\) containing expected NOESY peaks)LN
EL
SL
(     is created. Only distances between atoms where the)LN
EL
SL
(     chemical shift is known \(see ReadShift\) lead to)LN
EL
SL
(     an entry in the peak list.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The fourth option determines whether the found)LN
EL
SL
(     distances are added to the display as upper distance)LN
EL
SL
(     limits.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     Only distances that appear in a minimal number of)LN
EL
SL
(     structures given as third argument appear in the)LN
EL
SL
(     report and peak list.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The optional last two arguments give the names of)LN
EL
SL
(     two properties, only pairs where the first atom has)LN
EL
SL
(     the first of these properties and the second atom)LN
EL
SL
(     has the second one are considered. The default)LN
EL
SL
(     corresponds to pairs where both atoms are selected.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     In the report produced by this command, a table of)LN
EL
SL
(     distances will be created for each set of molecules)LN
EL
SL
(     with the same structure. A '+' sign indicates that)LN
EL
SL
(     the short distance is present in the molecule)LN
EL
SL
(     corresponding to the column, a '*' marks the smallest)LN
EL
SL
(     of these distances. The '+' sign is replaced by a '5')LN
EL
SL
(     for molecules 5, 15, 25, ... and by a '0' for)LN
EL
SL
(     molecules 10, 20, 30, ...)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     This command supports groups.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(EXAMPLE)LN
EL
