SL
()LN
EL
SL
(NAME)LN
EL
SL
(     CalcHbond - find H-bonds)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(SYNOPSIS)LN
EL
SL
(     CalcHbond expr expr expr)LN
EL
SL
(         \( 0 | 1 \) \( 0 | 1 \) \( 0 | 1 \) \( 0 | 1 \))LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(DESCRIPTION)LN
EL
SL
(     Find pairs of selected atoms where the first one is)LN
EL
SL
(     a donor and the second one an acceptor for an H-bond,)LN
EL
SL
(     the distance between the two atoms is smaller than)LN
EL
SL
(     the first argument, and the angle between the line)LN
EL
SL
(     from the atom connected to the donor and the donor)LN
EL
SL
(     and the line from the atom connected to the donor)LN
EL
SL
(     and the acceptor is smaller than the second argument.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The first option determines whether H-bonds within)LN
EL
SL
(     structures or H-bonds between atoms of different)LN
EL
SL
(     structures are desired.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     Depending on the other three options, the command will)LN
EL
SL
(     create a report with the H-bonds, a macro to add the)LN
EL
SL
(     H-bonds to all selected structures \(can e. g. be used)LN
EL
SL
(     to add them to a mean structure later\) and will add)LN
EL
SL
(     them to the display. Only H-bonds that appear in a)LN
EL
SL
(     minimal number of structures given as third argument)LN
EL
SL
(     appear in the report and the macro.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     In the report produced by this command, a table of)LN
EL
SL
(     H-bonds will be created for each set of molecules)LN
EL
SL
(     with the same structure. A '+' sign indicates that the)LN
EL
SL
(     H-bond is present in the molecule corresponding to)LN
EL
SL
(     the column. The '+' sign is replaced by a '5' for)LN
EL
SL
(     molecules 5, 15, 25, ... and by a '0' for molecules)LN
EL
SL
(     10, 20, 30, ...)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     This command supports groups.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(EXAMPLE)LN
EL
SL
(     CalcHbond 2.4 35 10 0 1 0 1)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(SEE ALSO)LN
EL
SL
(     SelectAtom, Group, AddHbond, RemoveDist)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(DATE)LN
EL
SL
(     981101)LN
EL

