SL
()LN
EL
SL
(NAME)LN
EL
SL
(     CalcRmsd - calculate RMSDs and displacements)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(SYNOPSIS)LN
EL
SL
(     CalcRmsd \( fit_pairs | as_is \) region)LN
EL
SL
(         name name nameList name nameList nameList)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(DESCRIPTION)LN
EL
SL
(     Calculate RMSDs and displacements of all selected)LN
EL
SL
(     molecules. The first argument selects whether each)LN
EL
SL
(     pair of molecules is superimposed before calculating)LN
EL
SL
(     the RMSD, or whether the current orientation is)LN
EL
SL
(     used. This can be useful to calculate RMSDs of)LN
EL
SL
(     structures already overlaid with the Fit command.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The second arguments selects the residue range)LN
EL
SL
(     used for superposition when calculating global)LN
EL
SL
(     RMSDs and global displacements.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The third argument selects the name of the first)LN
EL
SL
(     property that is used for superposition. The user)LN
EL
SL
(     can either give a property defined with DefProp or)LN
EL
SL
(     one of the predefined properties. The RMSD values)LN
EL
SL
(     will be printed in the upper right part of the)LN
EL
SL
(     matrix. This property is also used for the)LN
EL
SL
(     superpositions when calculating displacements.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The forth argument selects the name of the second)LN
EL
SL
(     property that is used for superposition. The RMSD)LN
EL
SL
(     values will be printed in the lower left part of)LN
EL
SL
(     the matrix.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The fifth argument is a space separated list of)LN
EL
SL
(     property names. It defines the groups of molecules)LN
EL
SL
(     that are compared. All the molecules of a group)LN
EL
SL
(     must be given a common property with DefPropMol)LN
EL
SL
(     \(e. g. g1 and g2\), and the list of these properties)LN
EL
SL
(     must be given here.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The sixth argument is the name of a property of the)LN
EL
SL
(     molecule that is used as reference for displacements)LN
EL
SL
(     and local RMSDs, typically the mean structure. If no)LN
EL
SL
(     name is given, average pairwise values will be)LN
EL
SL
(     calculated.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The seventh argument is a space separated list of)LN
EL
SL
(     property names. The global displacements will be)LN
EL
SL
(     calculated for all the given properties. The)LN
EL
SL
(     property used for the superposition is always)LN
EL
SL
(     the one given as third argument.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The eighth argument is a space separated list of)LN
EL
SL
(     property names. The local RMSDs will be calculated)LN
EL
SL
(     for all the given properties. The local RMSD of a)LN
EL
SL
(     residue is calculated by superimposing 3 residues)LN
EL
SL
(     centered at the given residue, using the property)LN
EL
grestore

