()LN
EL
SL
(NAME)LN
EL
SL
(     CalcSecondary - calculate secondary structure)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(SYNOPSIS)LN
EL
SL
(     CalcSecondary)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(DESCRIPTION)LN
EL
SL
(     Calculate the secondary structure of a protein)LN
EL
SL
(     using the algorithm published by Kabsch/Sander.)LN
EL
SL
(     The command operates on all selected residues)LN
EL
SL
(     of all selected molecules. It will set various)LN
EL
SL
(     properties on these residues, depending on the)LN
EL
SL
(     secondary structure. These properties are listed)LN
EL
SL
(     in a text window. They are used by the AddRibbon)LN
EL
SL
(     command to produce schematic drawings.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     Note that editing the text has no effect on the)LN
EL
SL
(     definitons used. For changing the definitons it)LN
EL
SL
(     is most convenient to use the WriteSecondary)LN
EL
SL
(     command.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     Since the calculation is based on hydrogen bonding)LN
EL
SL
(     patterns, the coordinates of HN atoms are required.)LN
EL
SL
(     So before using the command for a structure without)LN
EL
SL
(     coordinates for hydrogen atoms \(X-ray\), use the)LN
EL
SL
(     CalcAtom command for adding them.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(EXAMPLE)LN
EL
SL
(     CalcSecondary)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(SEE ALSO)LN
EL
SL
(     SelectMol, SelectRes, CalcAtom,)LN
EL
SL
(     DefPropRes, WriteSecondary, AddRibbon)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(DATE)LN
EL
SL
(     960815)LN
EL

