SL
()LN
EL
SL
(NAME)LN
EL
SL
(     CalcShift - calculate ring current shifts)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(SYNOPSIS)LN
EL
SL
(     CalcShift \( 1 | 0 \) \( 1 | 0\) string expr expr)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(DESCRIPTION)LN
EL
SL
(     Calculate ring current and bond polarization shifts of)LN
EL
SL
(     all selected atoms, taking into account all)LN
EL
SL
(     rings/atoms of the same molecule.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The first argument selects whether ring current shifts)LN
EL
SL
(     should be calculated, the second one whether bond)LN
EL
SL
(     polarization shifts should be calculated. At least one)LN
EL
SL
(     of the two should be selected, a warning is issued)LN
EL
SL
(     otherwise.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The third argument gives the name of the model for the)LN
EL
SL
(     calculation. The description of the models is read)LN
EL
SL
(     from the file:)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(         $MOLMOLHOME/setup/RingShift)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The fourth argument selects a cutoff, contributions to)LN
EL
SL
(     the ring current shifts above this value are listed)LN
EL
SL
(     individually *before* the sum.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The fifth argument gives a maximal distance for the)LN
EL
SL
(     atoms considered for the calculation of bond)LN
EL
SL
(     polarization shifts. Larger values will lead to longer)LN
EL
SL
(     calculation times.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The results are listed for each molecule separately,)LN
EL
SL
(     a summary with average, minimal and maximal values is)LN
EL
SL
(     given at the end.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     For all protons but HN, a ring belonging to the same)LN
EL
SL
(     residue as the proton is not considered for the)LN
EL
SL
(     calculation of the ring current shift.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The same is the case for the bond polarization: atoms)LN
EL
SL
(     of the same residue are not considred for the field)LN
EL
SL
(     calculation, except for HN atoms. A more elaborate)LN
EL
SL
(     strategy would have to be used to make the calculated)LN
EL
SL
(     numbers more useful as expected difference to random)LN
EL
SL
(     coil shift, especially for HN atoms.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(EXAMPLE)LN
EL
SL
(     CalcShift 1 0 Heigh-Mallion 0.5 5.0)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(REFERENCE)LN
EL
SL
(     Case, DA.)LN
EL
SL
(     Calibration of ring-current effects in proteins and)LN
EL
SL
(     nucleic acids.)LN
EL
SL
(     Journal of Biomolecular NMR, 6 \(1995\) 341-346)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
grestore

