()LN
EL
SL
(NAME)LN
EL
SL
(     CalcSurface - calculate solvent accessible surface)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(SYNOPSIS)LN
EL
SL
(     CalcSurface expr expr)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(DESCRIPTION)LN
EL
SL
(     Generate a report with solvent accessible surfaces)LN
EL
SL
(     of each residue. The first argument gives the radius)LN
EL
SL
(     of the solvent, the second the desired precision.)LN
EL
SL
(     A reasonably good approximation will be obtained with)LN
EL
SL
(     precisions of 2 or 3, higher values will lead to even)LN
EL
SL
(     better results.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     Only selected atoms are used for the calculation. The)LN
EL
SL
(     first surface given for each residue is the accessible)LN
EL
SL
(     surface in the context of the molecule, the second one)LN
EL
SL
(     is the surface of the isolated residue.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The results are listed for each molecule separately,)LN
EL
SL
(     a summary with average, minimal and maximal values is)LN
EL
SL
(     given at the end. If not all molecules have the same)LN
EL
SL
(     structure, or if not the same atoms are selected in)LN
EL
SL
(     all molecules, these values will not make much sense.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The calculation will take some time, especially if a)LN
EL
SL
(     high precision is desired. The time grows exponentially)LN
EL
SL
(     with the precision, so values of more than 4 or 5 are)LN
EL
SL
(     not recommended.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     This command supports groups.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(EXAMPLE)LN
EL
SL
(     CalcSurface 1.4 2)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(SEE ALSO)LN
EL
SL
(     SelectAtom, Group, AddSurface)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(DATE)LN
EL
SL
(     960317)LN
EL

