SL
()LN
EL
SL
(NAME)LN
EL
SL
(     DefPropMol   - define molecule property)LN
EL
SL
(     DefPropRes   - define residue property)LN
EL
SL
(     DefPropAtom  - define atom property)LN
EL
SL
(     DefPropBond  - define bond property)LN
EL
SL
(     DefPropAngle - define angle property)LN
EL
SL
(     DefPropDist  - define distance property)LN
EL
SL
(     DefPropPrim  - define primitive property)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(SYNOPSIS)LN
EL
SL
(     DefPropMol propertyName expr)LN
EL
SL
(     DefPropRes propertyName expr)LN
EL
SL
(     DefPropAtom propertyName expr)LN
EL
SL
(     DefPropBond propertyName expr)LN
EL
SL
(     DefPropAngle propertyName expr)LN
EL
SL
(     DefPropDist propertyName expr)LN
EL
SL
(     DefPropPrim propertyName expr)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(DESCRIPTION)LN
EL
SL
(     Define a property with the given name by the given)LN
EL
SL
(     expression. See SelectMol for a description of the)LN
EL
SL
(     expression syntax. Properties can be used in other)LN
EL
SL
(     property definitions or selections. The Select)LN
EL
SL
(     commands are actually just special cases of the)LN
EL
SL
(     DefProp commands, they defines the property with)LN
EL
SL
(     the name "selected". The following properties are)LN
EL
SL
(     used internally by the program and should not be)LN
EL
SL
(     defined by this command:)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(         all)LN
EL
SL
(         visible)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The value of the "visible" property is maintained)LN
EL
SL
(     by the program, it is set for all atoms, bonds,)LN
EL
SL
(     distances and primitives that have their attributes)LN
EL
SL
(     \(Style*\) set in a way to make them visible. This is)LN
EL
SL
(     very convenient for selecting only visible items.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The "displayed" property is used by the program to)LN
EL
SL
(     decide which items should be displayed. It is not)LN
EL
SL
(     recommended to modify it, it is normally better to)LN
EL
SL
(     use the Style* commands for changing the visibility.)LN
EL
SL
(     It is very useful for molecules, however, but the)LN
EL
SL
(     molecule dialog \(DialMol command\) is more convenient)LN
EL
SL
(     for modifying it in this case.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The "movable" property is used by the program to)LN
EL
SL
(     decide which items are moved by rotations etc.)LN
EL
SL
(     It only has an influence for molecules, and the)LN
EL
SL
(     molecule dialog \(DialMol command\) command is more)LN
EL
SL
(     convenient for modifying it.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     Some properties are predefined, they can be seen)LN
EL
SL
(     in the file:)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(         $MOLMOLHOME/setup/PropDef)LN
EL
