SL
()LN
EL
SL
(NAME)LN
EL
SL
(     DialColor - switch color dialog on and off)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(SYNOPSIS)LN
EL
SL
(     DialColor \( off | on \))LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(DESCRIPTION)LN
EL
SL
(     Switch color dialog on and off. The color dialog)LN
EL
SL
(     is a convenient interface to the commands BackColor,)LN
EL
SL
(     ColorAtom, ColorBond, ColorDist, TintDist, ColorPrim)LN
EL
SL
(     and TintPrim.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The central part of the dialog shows the currently)LN
EL
SL
(     chosen color. A selection of commonly used colors is)LN
EL
SL
(     available from the list on the right side of the)LN
EL
SL
(     dialog. These colors can also be selected by typing)LN
EL
SL
(     their name in the top text field on the left side.)LN
EL
SL
(     Arbitrary colors can be chosen by typing their RGB)LN
EL
SL
(     \(Red-Green-Blue\) components in the range 0.0 to 1.0)LN
EL
SL
(     in the corresponding text fields on the left side of)LN
EL
SL
(     the dialog.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     When an interactive selection is made in the drawing)LN
EL
SL
(     area, the dialog reflects the color of the selected)LN
EL
SL
(     item.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The currently chosen color can be applied to selected)LN
EL
SL
(     items by activating the corresponding button from the)LN
EL
SL
(     bottom of the dialog.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The OK button closes the dialog, the Help button shows)LN
EL
SL
(     this help page.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The list of colors displayed in the dialog is taken)LN
EL
SL
(     from the file:)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(         $MOLMOLHOME/setup/ColorList)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     An alternate file can be chosen with the PathNames)LN
EL
SL
(     command. An extensive list of colors is supplied in)LN
EL
SL
(     the file:)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
