()LN
EL
SL
(NAME)LN
EL
SL
(     DialRmsd - switch RMSD dialog on and off)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(SYNOPSIS)LN
EL
SL
(     DialRmsd \( off | on \) [ expr ])LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(DESCRIPTION)LN
EL
SL
(     Switch RMSD dialog on and off. The RMSD dialog is a)LN
EL
SL
(     convenient interface to the commands Fit and CalcRmsd,)LN
EL
SL
(     especially for comparisons of different molecules.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The optional second argument gives the number of)LN
EL
SL
(     groups of molecules for which residue ranges can be)LN
EL
SL
(     selected in the dialog. The default is the number of)LN
EL
SL
(     different molecules loaded.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The top two parts of the dialog allow selection of the)LN
EL
SL
(     two properties for which the global RMSDs are)LN
EL
SL
(     calculated. The common choices 'bb' \(backbone\) and)LN
EL
SL
(     'heavy' \(all heavy atoms\) can be selected directly.)LN
EL
SL
(     A different property can be selected by chosing the)LN
EL
SL
(     'other' button, and entering the name of the property)LN
EL
SL
(     in the corresponding text field on the right hand)LN
EL
SL
(     side.  If 'other' is selected, and the text field is)LN
EL
SL
(     left empty, no global RMSDs will be calculated.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The third part of the dialog is for entering residue)LN
EL
SL
(     ranges used for superposition. Different ranges can be)LN
EL
SL
(     used for different sets of molecules given by the)LN
EL
SL
(     range in the left side text field, this is useful for)LN
EL
SL
(     comparing different molecules. Both molecule ranges)LN
EL
SL
(     and residue ranges are given in the short selection)LN
EL
SL
(     syntax, e. g. 3-10,15,18-23. The number of lines for)LN
EL
SL
(     molecule ranges is chosen when opening the dialog, and)LN
EL
SL
(     can only be changed by closing the dialog and opening)LN
EL
SL
(     it again.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The check boxes in the fourth part of the dialog)LN
EL
SL
(     select the properties that global displacements, local)LN
EL
SL
(     RMSDs, and local displacements are calculated for.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The check boxes at the bottom of the dialog select)LN
EL
SL
(     some options. The first one has to be activated when a)LN
EL
SL
(     fit with segments in a different order than their)LN
EL
SL
(     residue numbering is desired, see the Fit help page)LN
EL
SL
(     for more details. The remaining options are used for)LN
EL
SL
(     RMSD calculation. They select whether each pair of)LN
EL
SL
(     molecules is fitted before calculating the RMSDs,)LN
EL
SL
(     whether local RMSDs and displacements should be)LN
EL
SL
(     reported relative to the mean structure or as average)LN
EL
SL
(     pairwise values, and whether RMSDs between groups of)LN
EL
SL
(     molecules \(as defined by the molecule ranges in the)LN
EL
SL
(     third part of the dialog\) should be calculated.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The buttons at the bottom right activate the Fit or)LN
EL
SL
(     CalcRmsd command with the selected options.)LN
EL
grestore

