()LN
EL
SL
(NAME)LN
EL
SL
(     DialSelect - switch selection dialog on and off)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(SYNOPSIS)LN
EL
SL
(     DialSelect \( off | on \))LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(DESCRIPTION)LN
EL
SL
(     Switch selection dialog on and off. The selection)LN
EL
SL
(     dialog is a convenient interface to the commands)LN
EL
SL
(     SelectMol, SelectRes, SelectAtom, SelectBond,)LN
EL
SL
(     SelectAngle and SelectDist.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     For making a selection, enter an expression \(see the)LN
EL
SL
(     Select* help page\) in one of the text fields, and)LN
EL
SL
(     either click the corresponding button on the left)LN
EL
SL
(     side, or hit the Return key\). When the Return key is)LN
EL
SL
(     used, the expression is stored in a history which can)LN
EL
SL
(     be recalled by the cursor keys or the small arrows on)LN
EL
SL
(     the right side of the text fields.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The button/field "R+A+B+A" makes a selection with the)LN
EL
SL
(     same expression for residues, atoms, bonds and angles.)LN
EL
SL
(     This can be convenient in some cases, also if the user)LN
EL
SL
(     is unsure what kind of selection a command requires.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The OK button closes the dialog, the Help button shows)LN
EL
SL
(     this help page.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(EXAMPLE)LN
EL
SL
(     DialSelect on)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(SEE ALSO)LN
EL
SL
(     Select*, DefProp*)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(DATE)LN
EL
SL
(     980409)LN
EL

