SL
()LN
EL
SL
(NAME)LN
EL
SL
(     Fit - calculate structure superpositions)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(SYNOPSIS)LN
EL
SL
(     Fit \( to_axes | to_first | circular | to_mean \))LN
EL
SL
(         nameList)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(DESCRIPTION)LN
EL
SL
(     Calculate a superposition of all selected molecules,)LN
EL
SL
(     using the selected atoms \(or the atoms with properties)LN
EL
SL
(     given by the second argument, see below\). The number)LN
EL
SL
(     of selected atoms of all selected molecules must be)LN
EL
SL
(     the same, otherwise an error message is issued.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     If the option 'to_axes' is selected, the principal)LN
EL
SL
(     axes of the structures are aligned to the axes of the)LN
EL
SL
(     coordinate system. This is useful for obtaining a)LN
EL
SL
(     standard orientation.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     If the option 'to_first' is selected, the RMSD of each)LN
EL
SL
(     structure to the first structure is minimized)LN
EL
SL
(     separately.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     If the option 'circular' is selected, the sum of the)LN
EL
SL
(     RMSDs from the first to the second, from the second to)LN
EL
SL
(     the third, ... and from the last to the first)LN
EL
SL
(     structure is minimized.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     If the option 'to_mean' is selected, the sum of all)LN
EL
SL
(     RMSDs to the resulting mean structure is minimized.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The options 'circular' and 'to_mean' use a less)LN
EL
SL
(     efficient algorithm than 'to_first', they can take)LN
EL
SL
(     very long to calculate. Their use is therefore)LN
EL
SL
(     generally not recommended. They can help in rare cases)LN
EL
SL
(     where the algorithm used in 'to_first' is numerically)LN
EL
SL
(     unstable.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     At least one molecule has to be selected for)LN
EL
SL
(     'to_axes', at least two for all other options.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     For only two selected molecules, all algorithms give)LN
EL
SL
(     the same result.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The RMSD to the mean averaged over all molecules for)LN
EL
SL
(     the selected atoms after the fit is printed on the)LN
EL
SL
(     status line.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The optional second argument gives a list of)LN
EL
SL
(     properties of atoms to be fitted, where the default)LN
EL
SL
(     is just all selected atoms. If several properties)LN
EL
SL
(     are given, the corresponding atoms are fitted in)LN
EL
SL
(     this order. This is useful when superimposing)LN
EL
SL
(     different molecules, and the fragments to be)LN
EL
SL
(     superimposed are not in the same order in all)LN
EL
SL
(     molecules. E. g. for superimposing fragments of)LN
EL
grestore

