SL
()LN
EL
SL
(NAME)LN
EL
SL
(     FlipAtom - flip atoms for better superposition)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(SYNOPSIS)LN
EL
SL
(     FlipAtom nameList)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(DESCRIPTION)LN
EL
SL
(     Exchanges sets of atom names in all selected)LN
EL
SL
(     residues if that leads to a better superposition to)LN
EL
SL
(     the first structure. The sets of atoms that can)LN
EL
SL
(     be exchanged is listed in the file:)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(         $MOLMOLHOME/setup/FlipAtoms)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The specifications in this file list atoms that)LN
EL
SL
(     are part of one potential exchange operation on one)LN
EL
SL
(     line. Each set of \(typically 2 or 3\) atoms that will)LN
EL
SL
(     be permuted by this operation is inside a pair of)LN
EL
SL
(     parentheses.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The atoms that can be exchanged are normally the)LN
EL
SL
(     atoms of rings that do not have a fixed orientation)LN
EL
SL
(     in an NMR structure \(PHE, TYR\), and the protons of)LN
EL
SL
(     methyl groups.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     This command is typcially used before calculating)LN
EL
SL
(     mean structures, or RMSDs that involve side chains.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The command will make a report listing the atoms)LN
EL
SL
(     that were exchanged.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(EXAMPLE)LN
EL
SL
(     FlipAtom "PHE TYR")LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(SEE ALSO)LN
EL
SL
(     PathNames, MeanMol, CalcRmsd)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(DATE)LN
EL
SL
(     950922)LN
EL

