SL
()LN
EL
SL
(NAME)LN
EL
SL
(     PaintSurface - set coloring style of surfaces)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(SYNOPSIS)LN
EL
SL
(     PaintSurface \( one_color | atom | dist | center |)LN
EL
SL
(         access | pot \) expr expr expr expr string)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(DESCRIPTION)LN
EL
SL
(     Set the coloring style of all selected surfaces.)LN
EL
SL
(     With the value one_color, the surface will be drawn)LN
EL
SL
(     entirely in the color set with ColorPrim.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     With the value atom, the color for each point is)LN
EL
SL
(     taken from the color of the closest selected atom.)LN
EL
SL
(     For this case, the third argument gives the maximum)LN
EL
SL
(     distance from the atom surface, the user will normally)LN
EL
SL
(     give the solvent radius used for calculating the)LN
EL
SL
(     surface for this argument.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     With the value dist, the color for each point is)LN
EL
SL
(     calculated from the smallest distance to a selected)LN
EL
SL
(     atom, using the mapping of values to colors described)LN
EL
SL
(     below.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     With the value center, the color for each point is)LN
EL
SL
(     calculated from the distance to the center of gravity)LN
EL
SL
(     of all selected atoms, using the mapping of values to)LN
EL
SL
(     colors described below.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     With the value access, the color for each point is)LN
EL
SL
(     calculated from the accessibility of the point, using)LN
EL
SL
(     the mapping of values to colors described below. The)LN
EL
SL
(     accessibility is calculated by an experimental \(and)LN
EL
SL
(     relatively slow\) algorithm that casts a number \(4**p,)LN
EL
SL
(     where p is the precision given as fifth argument\) of)LN
EL
SL
(     rays from each surface point, and counts how many of)LN
EL
SL
(     them intersect a selected atom within the distance)LN
EL
SL
(     range given by the second and third argument. A small)LN
EL
SL
(     offset given as fourth argument is normally applied to)LN
EL
SL
(     each surface point to avoid artefacts.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     With the value pot, the color is calculated from a)LN
EL
SL
(     potential field read with ReadPot, using the mapping)LN
EL
SL
(     of values to colors described below.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     For the options that require a mapping of values to)LN
EL
SL
(     colors, this mapping is given by the last argument.)LN
EL
SL
(     It consists of space separated tuples of the form:)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(         v r g b)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     where v is the potential and r, g, b give the color as)LN
EL
SL
(     RGB \(red, green, blue\) components. Colors are)LN
EL
SL
(     interpolated between the values in the table.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     Potentials have to be calculated with the CalcPot)LN
EL
grestore

