SL
()LN
EL
SL
(NAME)LN
EL
SL
(     PathNames - set path names)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(SYNOPSIS)LN
EL
SL
(     PathNames string string string string string)LN
EL
SL
(         string string string string)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(DESCRIPTION)LN
EL
SL
(     Set path names for some configuration files.)LN
EL
SL
(     Normally the program reads these file from the)LN
EL
SL
(     directory $MOLMOLHOME/setup.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The following is a list of all configuration files:)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(         AtomRadius: Contains radii for atoms. Used for)LN
EL
SL
(             the commands CalcBond and CheckBond.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(         AtomCharge: Contains charges for atoms. These)LN
EL
SL
(             are used when 'simplecharge' is referenced)LN
EL
SL
(             in an expression for an atom.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(         FlipAtoms: Contains sets of atoms that can be)LN
EL
SL
(             exchanged by the FlipAtom command.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(         RingShift: Contains definitions of models for)LN
EL
SL
(             the CalcShift command.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(         PdbAtoms: Contains a table that is used to)LN
EL
SL
(             translate atom names from PDB files to)LN
EL
SL
(             atom names from the residue library.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(         PropDef: Contains definitons of standard)LN
EL
SL
(             properties.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(         ResLib: Residue library.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(         MenuDir: Directory that contains menu definition)LN
EL
SL
(             files \(MenuBar, *.menu, Popup, Valuator\).)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(         ColorList: List of colors used for DialColor.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     Generally the configuration files are read when)LN
EL
SL
(     they are used the first time, and the contents is)LN
EL
SL
(     kept in memory. This means that changing the path)LN
EL
SL
(     only has an effect after leaving the program and)LN
EL
SL
(     starting it again. This is always true for MenuDir.)LN
EL
SL
(     It is also necessary for AtomRadius if the CalcBond)LN
EL
SL
(     or CheckBond command was used, for RingShift if the)LN
EL
SL
(     CalcShift command was used, for PdbAtoms if a PDB)LN
EL
SL
(     file was read or written, and for ColorList if the)LN
EL
SL
(     color dialog \(DialColor\) was opened.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     ResLib, together with AtomCharge, is read as soon as)LN
EL
SL
(     a molecule is read from a file. To use the new)LN
EL
SL
(     definitions after ResLib has been changed, the program)LN
EL
SL
(     has to be reinitialized by using the InitAll command,)LN
EL
grestore

