()LN
EL
SL
(NAME)LN
EL
SL
(     PlotPar - set plot parameters)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(SYNOPSIS)LN
EL
SL
(     PlotPar expr expr expr expr expr)LN
EL
SL
(         \( 0 | 1 \) \( 0 | 1 \) \( 0 | 1 \) \( 0 | 1 \))LN
EL
SL
(         expr expr expr)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(DESCRIPTION)LN
EL
SL
(     Set size and options for plots. The first argument)LN
EL
SL
(     gives the width of the paper, the second one the)LN
EL
SL
(     height. The third argument gives the width of the)LN
EL
SL
(     plot, the fourth one the height. If one of the plot)LN
EL
SL
(     sizes is 0, it is calculated to correspond to the)LN
EL
SL
(     dimensions \(aspect ratio\) of the window. The plot)LN
EL
SL
(     is centered on the paper.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The current unit for these sizes is shown in the)LN
EL
SL
(     prompt, it can be changed with the PlotUnit command.)LN
EL
SL
(     The default paper size also depends on the current)LN
EL
SL
(     unit.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The fifth argument selects the horizontal resolution)LN
EL
SL
(     used for saving image \(TIFF, JPEG, PNG\) files.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The first option switches stereo plotting on or off.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The second option switches shading and hidden surface)LN
EL
SL
(     elimination for the plot. The third only has an)LN
EL
SL
(     influence if shading is switched on. If it is)LN
EL
SL
(     selected, a full hidden surface elimination is done.)LN
EL
SL
(     This can take a few minutes for complex plots, but it)LN
EL
SL
(     is necessary to produce perfect results as soon as the)LN
EL
SL
(     scene contains spheres, cylinders or primitives. If it)LN
EL
SL
(     is not selected, a simple depth sorting is used, which)LN
EL
SL
(     is much faster, but the result can contain slight)LN
EL
SL
(     errors. For important plots \(publications\), this)LN
EL
SL
(     option must always be switched on.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The fourth option selects whether the plot is)LN
EL
SL
(     rotated by 90 degrees to produce a landscape plot.)LN
EL
SL
(     Note that the size of the plot \(arguments 3 and 4\))LN
EL
SL
(     is still given in the original orientation of the)LN
EL
SL
(     plot, before rotation. The size of the paper is)LN
EL
SL
(     given in the orientation used by the printer, which)LN
EL
SL
(     is normally portrait. So e. g. good size for a)LN
EL
SL
(     landscape plot on A3 format are 29.7 42 0 26.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The third but last parameter select the precision)LN
EL
SL
(     \(resolution\) of the plot. See DrawPrec for an)LN
EL
SL
(     explanation of this parameter.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The second but last parameter selects a gamma correction)LN
EL
SL
(     parameter. 1.0 will leave the colors unchanged, values)LN
EL
SL
(     less than 1.0 will make the colors brighter, values)LN
EL
SL
(     greater than 1.0 will make the colors darker. Note)LN
EL
