()LN
EL
SL
(NAME)LN
EL
SL
(     WriteSecondary - write macro with secondary structure)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(SYNOPSIS)LN
EL
SL
(     WriteSecondary)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(DESCRIPTION)LN
EL
SL
(     Show a macro that describes the current definiton of)LN
EL
SL
(     secondary structure for all selected residues. Exactly)LN
EL
SL
(     one molecule must be selected. This macro can be)LN
EL
SL
(     edited and saved to a given file name. The macro can)LN
EL
SL
(     be executed with XMacUser to set the same \(modified\))LN
EL
SL
(     secondary structure again.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(     The secondary structure can be read from a PDB file,)LN
EL
SL
(     calculated with CalcSecondary, or set manually with a)LN
EL
SL
(     set of DefPropRes and SetNeigh commands. The most)LN
EL
SL
(     convenient way is often to use CalcSecondary to get an)LN
EL
SL
(     intial definition, then use WriteSecondary to create a)LN
EL
SL
(     macro, edit it to the "correct" definitions, and then)LN
EL
SL
(     use XMacUser to set these.)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(EXAMPLE)LN
EL
SL
(     WriteSecondary)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(SEE ALSO)LN
EL
SL
(     ReadPdb, CalcSecondary, XMacUser, AddRibbon)LN
EL
SL
()LN
EL
SL
(DATE)LN
EL
SL
(     951010)LN
EL

